And in That, very Prayer, alſo, Chriſt ſeemeth to Act, as at his Going to the Feaſt of Tabernacles; 

                  •
               ot Openly, but, as it were, Secretly. And ſo, he prayeth for the World alſo. That they may know God hath ſent him: and hath Loved His; as he Loved Him. And he Plainly ſaith, that To know God, and Chriſt, is Life Eternall. Which is yet promiſed to All: and All ſhall Know my Name.
